      <biogHist id="md5-85d8d03f7ead3e63915ef032311f27a5">
        <p>Historian, 1917- .  Dr. Eccles joined the University as an assistant professor of history in 1957 and became an associate professor in 1959.  From 1963 to 1983 he served as professor of history at the University of Toronto. An expert on the history of New France, he is the author of several books, including Frontenac: The Courtier Governor (1959) and Canada Under Louis XIV (1965), which were written while he was teaching at the University of Alberta.</p>
      </biogHist>
